  "text": "Two of the four adult females found active on the ground had distinctly extended oviducts, whereas in the remaining two females, oviducts were hypertrophied but not much extended. Values of condition index (defined as [BW/ distinctly smaller that those in the latter (2.07 and 2.22), and were within the range of corresponding values in the three nesting females (1.41-1.90). These may suggest that only the former two females bred in 1995, and that the reproductive frequency in mature females of the Kita-kojima population of E. elegans is lower than annual as in some insular populations of E. okadae (see [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] ).",
